{"lemma":"زَقَّ","slug":"زَقَّ","root":"ز.ق.ق","root_slug":"ز-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-ق-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17894","n17895"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wineskin","examples":[{"text":"طَرِبَ الشيْخُ فغنّى، واصْطبحْ\nمن عُقارٍ تُنهبُ الهمّ الفَرَحْ\nأخَذتْ من كلّ شيءٍ لَوْنَهــا،\nهي في ناجودها قوْسُ قُزَحْ\nشيْخُ لذّاتٍ، نقِيٌّ عِرْضُهُ،\nتحْسُنُ الأشعارُ فيه، والمِدَحْ.\nلا تراهُ الدّهْرُ إلاّ ثَمِلاً،\nبينَ إبْريقٍ، وزِقٍّ، وقدَحْ","english":"The shaykh gleed and sang and craved more booze\nforthy delight removes the sorrow.\nHe obtained from every thing its hues\nand his cup exposed a rainbow.\nShaykh of bliss, no way blammed,\nThe notes of him are merry, fele to plaud,\nFate sees him not but slammed,\nbetwixe ewer and wineskin, beaker-pawed."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to feed with one’s bill"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to push, to press, to urge"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of زَقَّ (zaqqa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"darter, Anhinga gen. et spp.","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic זִיקָּא (zīqā) / ܙܸܩܵܐ (zeqqā).\n\nOnomatopoeic or from the thought that the chicks get fed from a زِقّ (ziqq, “waterskin”) where the grub is stored."},"ipa":["/ziqq/","/zaq.qa/","/zaqq/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17894","headword_ar":"زُقٌّ","root":"zq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"one of the names of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Moheet, K: *) pl., as in the Moheet,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziqaqapN","text_ar":"زِقَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but accord. to the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaqaqapN","text_ar":"زَقَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n17895","headword_ar":"زِقٌّ","root":"zq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A skin for holding wine &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any receptacle, consisting of a skin, that is used for wine and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, not thus called unless it be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stripped off from the part next the animal's neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to AHn,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one in which wine is conveyed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skin for water"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"milk;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siqaA='N","text_ar":"سِقَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a skin of which the hair is clipped, not plucked out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for wine and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for wine &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a receptacle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZarofN","text_ar":"ظَرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb, and Har p. 335,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of skin, in which are put clarified butter and vinegar and wine:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har ibid.:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zarof","text_ar":"ظَرْف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smeared with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zifot","text_ar":"زِفْت"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) AHát says that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is smeared with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zifot","text_ar":"زِفْت"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiyr","text_ar":"قِير"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. (of pauc., S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azoqaAqN","text_ar":"اَزْقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^azuq~N","text_ar":"اَزُقٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by El-Hejeree, (M,) and (of mult., S)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ziqaAqN","text_ar":"زِقَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuq~aAnN","text_ar":"زُقَّانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK erroneously written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruq~AqN","text_ar":"رُقّاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, M, Msb, K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","S","K","Lth","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}